image_analysis.description: A photograph taken from a doorway looking into a walk-in closet. The closet has cedar wood plank walls and a dark wood parquet floor with a geometric pattern. A single round light fixture is mounted on the ceiling. There are two hanging rods: one in the back and one on the right side, both filled with various coats and jackets. Several pairs of shoes and boots are lined up on the floor against the back wall. A small white piece of paper is taped to the right wall above the clothes rack. The doorway is framed by white trim.
image_analysis.layout: Interior photograph of a closet space.

stamps_or_markings: Bates stamp 'EFTA00000976' in the bottom right corner

notes: The image is a photograph of a closet, likely part of an evidentiary record as indicated by the Bates stamp. There is a small white paper on the wall inside the closet, but the text on it is illegible due to distance and resolution.
